The Google Assistant platform has some new features that are bound to get people excited. The tech giants have launched six new voices to choose from for Google Assistant for Android phones and Google Home. One of those voices is the voice of celebrity soul singer John Legend. In reaction to this news, the soul singer’s wife Christine Teigen went to Twitter to say “I don’t even need human John anymore” I don’t even need human John anymore https://t.co/qF885WtXdp — christine teigen (@chrissyteigen) May 8, 2018  As an added feature, you can assign different Google Assistant voices to respond to different people. To do this, you have to program the Google Assistant to recognise the voices of the different people speaking. Google Assistant already has one male and one female voice to choose from and this update brings the number options up to eight. 